# Trading Domain

Read `.ai/trading/architecture.md` for the full pipeline.

## Entry vs exit legs (mandatory)

Deal `direction`: `long` (buy→sell) | `short` (sell→buy).

| Leg | Job | Service |
|-----|-----|---------|
| entry | `MonitorOrderJob` | `OrderMonitoringService` |
| exit | `ManageExitJob` | `ExitManagementService` |

Do not apply entry logic to exit-leg orders. Use `Deal::entrySide()` / `exitSide()` in deal context.

## Scopes

- `TradingOrder::entry()` / `exit()` → raw exchange side (legacy)
- `TradingOrder::entryLeg()` → first deal leg (buy long, sell short)
- `monitorable()` must be combined with `entryLeg()` when dispatching `MonitorOrderJob`

## Locks

Use `Cache::lock` with `config('trading.lock_ttl')` for order/deal/market mutations.
